external_knowledge:
- 'garden of opportunity' refers to the jobs and experience levels available in the current job market;
- 'blossoms within our reach' indicates that the job is accessible to us and meets the criteria set;
- 'bearing a fruit sweeter than 60,000 USD' refers to jobs with a salary in USD higher than 60,000;
- 'doors still wide open and welcoming' signifies that the job status is 'open' and available for applications;
- 'harvest season yet to come' means the application deadline has not been reached and is in the future.

sql:
SELECT j.job_title
FROM jobs j
WHERE j.salary > (SELECT AVG(salary) FROM jobs);

external_knowledge:
Seasoned sailors: Refers to senior engineers (SE); 
Vast ocean of employment: The job market;
Anchored to the shores of full-time office work: Jobs with full-time in-office requirements (remote_ratio = 0);
Salary anchors: Represents the salary thresholds;
Average depth for vessels in their own maritime regions: Average salary for jobs in the same category.

- 'up' means the job posting status is 'open'; 
- 'half-time remote work plan' refers to a remote ratio of 50%; 
- 'average pay' is the average salary in USD; 
- 'above the least offered salary' means the average salary must be more than the minimum salary in the salaries table.
